Finally with dine in being introduced again, it was nice stopping in somewhere and not eating in the cold. Love the creativity and potential they have. We got the burrata pizza and the elote style pizza.  One more traditional and the other a new concept, both delicious. They nailed the elote flavor, literally tastes like elote on pizza, very well executed. Burrata pizza was out favorite, nice touch with truffle oil and then some lemon to balance it perfectly. HOWEVER, when I passed the desk later that evening I was handed a small plastic pizza cutter(still pre-wrapped) which had originally been delivered with my food. It had slipped out of a tear in the fold of the paper bag that my breadsticks were in. The food had been briefly left at the desk because covid and the cutter was presumably lost in that time. Also the breadsticks were baller, for the record.  I ordered several pizzas yesterday I’ve been munching on since, all of them excellent & they keep well. On a warm Saturday in December, my husband and I decided to walk to the River North Parlor Pizza location for brunch with our 5 month old son before visiting Santa. The restaurant opens at 10:30am on Saturdays and we arrived at 10:45am, to an EMPTY restaurant. Upon arrival, we were informed that we could not have our stroller on the floor and that our son could either sit in a high chair or they could give us a sling for a car seat.  We explained that these options would not work for us because our baby was not yet big enough to sit in a high chair, nor was the seat on our stroller a removable car seat. Not one, but two employees confirmed that we would not be able to dine there with a stroller at the table. This was very disheartening especially considering that we were the ONLY customers in the very large restaurant, and there were plenty of options for seating us at a table where we would be out of the way. We made a reservation for fourteen at parlor to meet with friends and watch the bears game while we were in town for the weekend and had an excellent time.  We arrived early and the bartender took care of us until we were seated.  Our server was excellent and kept drinks refilled and made sure everyone had what they needed, she was also helpful with recommendations and was knowledgeable of the menu.  We started with pizza bread, which was delicious.  It was super moist and topped with cheese and pepperoni.  We had a couple orders of kale and artichoke dip as well which came with toast.  It was creamy and neither the kale or artichoke was overpowering, but added great texture and flavor to the dip.  My gf ordered the “You Burrata be Kidding me” pizza, which was a big hit at the table, though I didn’t try it.  She said it was delicious and that the crust was prepared perfectly.  I had the French toast with berries, which, admittedly, was like a dessert, but I was not complaining.  The bread was brioche and the topping was excellent.  We’re not drinkers, but the Bloody Mary bar looked very well stocked, and many at the table had mimosas with a variety of juice options.  It was a great experience, and, despite the outcome of the game, it was a great place to congregate and watch

I just had their pepperoni pizza (Sgt. Pepper) via delivery (UberEats). I know people LOVE this pizza parlor, so I wanted to know what all the fuss was about. From what I can tell, there’s nothing particularly unique or even above average about the pizza itself, for a few reasons:  It is SO oily, more so than any pizza I’ve had in years. I had to mop up the oil with a napkin just to make it tolerable, losing much of the sauce because you only get an occasional cluster of cheese.  The crust was nice-not too thin, not too thick, but comparable to other crusts in Chicago. The flavor of the pepperoni was better than most, but if the pepperoni created the excess oil, not worth it. Also, you’re unlikely to get a single bite that includes pepperoni, cheese AND sauce, but all bites will have oil. All in all, the pepperoni pros are not enough to overcome all the other cons.  Also, they do not precut the pizza for delivery, and instead send a plastic pizza cutter. Cute but not practical, I ended up using my own slicer. That was annoying in it of itself, but if they HAD precut, maybe more of the oil would have been absorbed by the cardboard, and it would’ve tasted better.  I ate it, but I don’t feel great about it.
Awesome pizza and atmosphere! I've been going to the one in West loop for a few years which I love but this is much more convenient since I live in River north

This little cute restaurant was perfect. Me, my husband, and baby went here for Mother’s Day while visiting Chicago and I fell in love with the atmosphere and the friendly staff. The food was good and the drinks were better. I highly suggest the Bloody Mary bar and mimosas if you’re in to that. However, they do come around a lot, ridding the table of trash as you eat. So if you’re wanting to keep something, let them know. Enjoy!
I didn't wait long for a table and the food came out quickly. The pizzas are top and I wish I eat the air, it smells amazing. I believe the menus are the same across locations so just go to one.
Lots of fun every time I come here, upbeat atmosphere and the pizza is awesome

Fantastic service, great menu.  My server was fast, attentive, timely; bussers and food runners also very customer friendly and attentive.  Food came out very quickly, and was delicious!  Great experience, I highly recommend!
They have the most delicious  food and drinks and Chicago period
Simply the best!!!
Great pizza,  great appetizers,  gets a little loud but the place is huge so it's too be expected

Super delicious, and the service was prompt and polite! I loved the Honey Boo Boo, which had Honey and whole garlic cloves. The crust had an amazing texture. It was very loud in the restaurant though, so you might have trouble hearing people

An excellent new location. It has plenty of space, and a great area available for parties or events. Their pizza is great, other food as well, and they have a really good beer selection. Highly recommend this new location.

Absolute pleasure coming here!! You KNOW a place is great when they’re a pizza place, and their burgers turn out being one of the best I’ve ever had!!  Service was outstanding. Very nice, and helpful staff. Managers checked on us to make sure food was great.  FAST FAST FSAT delivery on the food as well. Food was to our table in a matter of minutes.  GO HERE. It will blow you away! Well done.. well done..
So great! Perfectly curated menu, not an over abundance of choices but with plenty of choices. Vegetarian friendly, delicious hummus, frites, and fried burrata 🤤
Good experience
Pizza was awesome, beer selection was solid, staff was very friendly.

Their outside patio is super nice and is just a really relaxing addition to River North. The wait staff was really nice and accommodating and the food was very tasty. They have good lunch options with a pizza and a side for one price. The portions are big and can easily be split between multiple people. I got the brussel sprout pizza and the fried mozzarella (Yum!) and split it with one other person but a third person could have easily shared with us. The dessert tacos are so good!! But also something I recommend spitting since they're huge!
Great food and service.
Margharita pizza awesome!! Cesar salad HORRIBLE
Food was a good experience!
Great atmosphere, and really good food. Would recommend!

Terribly uncomfortable bar stool seating. Not an ideal eatery if you are tall, curvy. Our team elected to have lunch here and we were all uncomfortable sitting at the table. Aside from the discomfort, the food is absolutely delicious and great service!!!
Not bad, service can be slow.
Loved it !
Love this place. Love the food and the drinks and the service but was the plastic cups and straws really necessary? No they’re not. Please please watch your   Single use plastic use
Fantastic and what a great venue to watch March Madness. Awesome food for my friends and I
I loved the salad  and pizza
Great pizza
Same as the other two. Decent thin crust. Good salads, especially the roasted beet. They have a big selection of beers and cocktails, but I don't drink so I have no opinions on that.
Great atmosphere, a little loud at dinner time, but super quick service, a great selection of pizzas and appetizers.  A good place to meet with coworkers it have a fun date!
Very good pizza and beer list
Pizzzzzzzzaaaaaaaaa love!
Not the best parlor but still very good

Really good pizza and absolutely delicious chicken sandwich. I was really impressed how fast our food arrived with how incredibly busy the place was. I was almost discouraged to order food when I saw how bust it was but the food was ready very quickly and it was good.
Great Security,Great Food!!!
Stand up pizza to go.  If you are looking for something to eat when the city is crowded.
Good variery of pizzas. Beer selection is decent. Plan to wait if you are going in peak hours during lunch or dinner time.
Avg. Nothing special. Wood pizzas good. Drinks avg.
Great non deep dish pizza!
Great serve, go see my girl Annie, best mixologist in Chicago! Love her!!

Went there for the first time on my birthday, and I’m so happy I did. Best pizza in Chicago hands down and the beer selection is awesome too. Place gets really loud, but the food makes it all worth it.
Great food just like the West loop location. Only issue, but a big one is the bar height chairs at the table really uncomfortable. Everyone at my table felt the same way about the chairs.
terrible
Love the west loop Parlor so glad this one came to River North!!

You have to specify that you want cheese on your pizza or it doesn’t come with any and it costs extra for any type of cheese. Horrible delivery surprise. However, this could be contributed to Uber Eat’s poor user interface.
Love the Parlor in the west loop and excited to have one closer to home in river north!!

Treated me like a criminal. Terrible customer service practices! .. My wife and I ordered drinks , Waitress said I need a credit card . I was puzzled as she took my credit card and never returned. When she finally came back I said you never gave me my card back. She said we keep it until you check out. I question this practice and she says it’s to make sure you pay without leaving. Really??  Do my wife and look like criminals? Yes she says every place around here does that! I said no I have been in Chicago 4 days and no restaurant has kept my credit card ! I actually walked across the street to Siena and sat at the bar and they didn’t keep my card! Hey Parlor HORRIBLE practice . Stop treating all your customers as thieves! 1star is a gift

This is a really cool spot with great and affordable food. I split the Aunt Childada's pizza with a friend and it was delicious. They also have an extensive drink menu. I went with a group of 5 people on a Saturday without a reservation. They told us it would be an hour wait, but we were seated within 20 minutes. There are also a lot of great places to take cool pictures there. The artwork and decorations are awesome. Outside of the restaurant there is a mural of wings that look like pizza slices. Fun place, definitely recommend.
Only went for the desert tacos, so I can't speak for the pizza ... but OMG!  WOW!  Dessert Tacos are to die for!
Food was excellent as always but man those stools are so uncomfortable!
Great pizza bar and a great spot for sunday funday or a weeknight of fun!
Fast service and great pizza
Horrible pizza !!! Go somewhere else
A++ quality service, great food and great drinks. Highly recommended!
Great food and atmosphere, horribly uncomfortable stools.  You think they’d learn about the stools the 3rd time around. Looking froward to the summer when you can use the big patio

Elitist, overpriced pizza place. They try to come off as hip and trendy but there’s no way this river north location is any different than the other high prices low value places around.  The place is so lowly lit you can barely read the menu. Might as well keep out your cell phone flashlight to see things.  The food is ok. They throw a bunch of weird toppings on a pizza and up charge $16 for a small bite because it can pass as a “craft” pizza. Very thin and typically burnt end crusts if you’re into that.  The kale and artichoke dip is actually a really good appetizer. . . Except that they give you half as much bread as you need. We asked for more and the waitress looked at us like we’re crazy. Pretty sure she never put the request in cause we asked again 10 minutes later then saw her put the order in. On top of all that they had the nerve to charge 2 more dollars for bread!!! Are you kidding me? Maybe don’t hand out child sized servings for a group dish.  Really not a fan of this place. Rather go somewhere with an upbeat atmosphere if I’m gonna be stuck paying river north prices.
Food was great! Burratta pizza was perfect. Manager discounted the check and gave our two kids complimentary desserts just because. Highly recommend
